GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15b: Compensation Review and Approval Process for Officers and Key Employees
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: COMPENSATION FOR THE OFFICERS OF THE SCHOOL FOR THE YEAR ENDED JUNE 30, 2010 WAS SETBY THE CHAIRMAN OF THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES AND THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD. THE CHAIRMAN WAS PROVIDED WITH THE SALARY HISTORY OF EACH OFFICER. THE SCHOOL PARTICIPATES IN AN EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION SURVEY OF NATIONAL, PEER SCHOOLS. THE RESULTS OF THIS SURVEY WERE PROVIDED TO THE CHAIRMAN ALONG WITH COMPENSATION FIGURES FOR OFFICERS AT OTHER, LOCAL SCHOOLS. THIS DATA WAS CONSIDERED IN SETTING THE COMPENSATION FOR THE OFFICERS OF THE SCHOOL. PROPOSED COMPENSATION FOR THE OFFICERS WAS REVIEWED BY THE CHAIRMAN OF THE BOARD WITH THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD. COMPENSATION WAS DOCUMENTED IN A WRITTEN EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE ENTIRE BOARD OF TRUSTEES IS REQUIRED by the Board's Bylaws TO DISCLOSE ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST ON AN ANNUAL BASIS. A signed conflict of interest statement from each board member is required before the first regular meeting each year. EMPLOYEES ARE NOT ALLOWED TO ENGAGE IN ADDITIONAL EMPLOYMENT THAT COMPETES WITH THE INTERESTS OF THE SCHOOL. THIS IS OUTLINED IN THE EMPLOYEE HANDBOOK.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11: Form 990 Review Process
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The information returns of the School are prepared and reviewed by Staff and the Schools external auditors. A draft of the 990 is then provided to the Audit Committee of the Board of Trustees for its review. The Committees questions and comments are addressed and incorporated. Once that review is complete, a copy of the return, excluding the Schedule of Contributors, is forwarded to each member of the Board of Trustees for his or her review. Once the Board of Trustees questions or comments are addressed and incorporated, the return is filed.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Line 6: Explanation of Classes of Members or Shareholder
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: There is one class of members. Members shall be (a) parents or legal guardians of currently registered students of the School who are identified as such on student contracts and (b) all current members of the Board of Trustees. Members who are not behind or in default with all the School's required tuition, dues, fees and assessments shall be members in good standing and may attend or vote at meetings of members. Even though a person may qualify multiple times as a member, i.e. by virtue of having more than one child enrolled at the School or by being a parent and a member of the Board, no person shall have more than one vote as a member.
